The lockindicator-applet is a GNOME applet which displays a notification when 
the Caps and Num Lock keys are on. Right now, it doesn't do it for the Num Lock
keys; all I need is to draw a not-too-naff icon for it.

The lockindicator-applet uses the custom typeutils and xkb modules (available
separately as well) and the python-keybinder module.
 

REQUIREMENTS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Python version >= 2.6
2. python-setuptools
3. doxygen (to produce documentation)
4. python-keybinder

WHAT DOES lockindicator-applet PRODUCE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Python binaries in /usr/local/bin/ (by default).
3. Libraries in /usr//local/lib/pythonX.y/dist-packages/ (by default).
4. Doxygenated documentation in /usr/share/doc/lockindicator-applet (refman.pdf)
5. python-keybinder. 